article.headline: Stetson 70, Savannah State 60
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Stetson senior guard E.J. Gordon scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Stetson to a 70-60 victory over Savannah State Thursday The Hatters overcame a 32-point effort by Savannah State junior guard Javon Randolph, who connected on 12 of 16 shots from the floor, including five of six 3-pointers. Stetson improved to 5-16 overall with its third straight victory. It was the first time in nearly two years that the Hatters had won three in a row. Savannah State fell to 2-22 in the non-conference loss. Gordon scored nine consecutive points after breaking a 3-3 tie in the early minutes. He tallied 15 points in the first half while helping Stetson to a 38-25 halftime lead. Stetson senior guard Anthony Register added 10 points and was the only other player in double figures. The Hatters led by as many as 23 points, 65-42, with 6:18 to play. However, the Tigers rallied back in the final minutes against Stetson's reserves, outscoring the Hatters 18-5 in that span. Randolph connected on four of five shots for eight points in the final six minutes.
